\int_{\gamma_{r}}\frac{1}{1+z^{2}}dz = \int_{0}^{\pi}\frac{ire^{it}}{1+r^{2}e^{2it}}dt
|\int_{0}^{\pi}\frac{ire^{it}}{1+r^{2}e^{2it}}dt| \leq \int_{0}^{\pi}|\frac{ire^{it}}{1+r^{2}e^{2it}}|dt \leq \int_{0}^{\pi}\frac{r}{r^{2}-1}dt = \frac{\pi r}{r^{2}-1}
\lim_{r \rightarrow + \infty }\frac{\pi r}{r^{2}-1} = 0
