\int_{C}\frac{1}{1+z^{2}} = \int_{-r}^{r}\frac{1}{1+x^{2}}dx + \int_{\gamma_{r}}\frac{1}{1+z^{2}} = 2\pi i \cdot Res(f,i) = 2\pi i \cdot \frac{1}{2i} = \pi
\lim_{r \rightarrow + \infty}\int_{-r}^{r}\frac{1}{1+x^{2}}dx
\int_{- \infty}^{+\infty}\frac{1}{1+x^{2}}dx = \pi
\int_{0}^{+\infty}\frac{1}{1+x^{2}}dx = \frac{\pi}{2}
